@startuml highway_ready_to_control_activation_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Highway Ready To Control Activation Signal Flow\n(route/cruise/lane context -> HWP -> long/lat control activation)

participant "NAV / cruise /\nlane-guide context" as PilotCtx #F4F7FB
participant "HWP\nhighway pilot owner" as HWP #E8F7E8
participant "Pilot state bus" as PilotBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Highway Readiness Inputs ==

PilotCtx -> HWP : navRouteClass\ncruiseState\nlaneGuideState\nattentionLevel\ndmsActive
HWP -> HWP : highwayReady =\n(navRouteClass == 2 and cruiseState >= 1 and attentionLevel <= 2)
HWP -> HWP : longCtrlActive =\n(highwayReady and cruiseState == 2)
HWP -> HWP : latCtrlActive =\n(highwayReady and laneGuideState >= 2)
HWP -> HWP : driverMonitorReq =\n(dmsActive == 1 and attentionLevel >= 2)
note right of HWP
Representative activation inputs
- navRouteClass
- cruiseState
- laneGuideState
- attentionLevel / dmsActive
end note

== Pilot State Publish ==

HWP -> PilotBus : frmHighwayPilotStateMsg\nHighwayPilotReady / LongCtrlActive / LatCtrlActive
HWP -> PilotBus : DriverMonitorReq / LaneGuideState / CruiseState
note right of HWP
Representative outputs
- HighwayPilotReady
- LongCtrlActive
- LatCtrlActive
- DriverMonitorReq
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

PilotBus -> Obs : highway pilot / control activation readback

note over PilotCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Route, cruise, and lane-guide context reach HWP
2. HWP decides whether highway mode is ready
3. HWP raises long/lat control activation when readiness is satisfied
4. Observers expose pilot activation and monitoring demand
end note

@enduml
